This paper discusses the functional and non-functional properties of blockchains, which are related to security, distributed computing, software engineering, databases, and networking. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
